"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-simone-biles-gymnastics-2024-usa-championships\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles won a record-extending ninth U.S. all-around title, plus won every individual event title at nationals for the second time in her career.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles took a dominant next step to what would be her third Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 152, \"to\": 229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 223, \"end\": 228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999994542577, \"rank\": 5.457341524390288e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won the all-around at the Xfinity U.S. Championships by 5.9 pointsover Skye Blakely, combining scores from Friday and Sunday in Fort Worth, Texas.\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 306, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skye_Blakely\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Skye Blakely\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skye_Blakely\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skye_Blakely\"}, {\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.5325131323155285e-16, \"text\": \"Fort Worth, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\"}, {\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.5325131323155285e-16, \"text\": \"Fort Worth, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The margin is greater than what separated second place from 10th place.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 453, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could not be more proud of how I am doing this time in the year and just gaining that confidence over and over, getting myself back in front of a crowd and just doing what I do in practice,\\\" Biles said.\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"XFINITY U.S. CHAMPIONSHIPS:Results  It's the third-largest margin of victory since the perfect 10 scoring system was replaced in 2006.\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles won by a record 6.55 points in 2018, when she also became the first woman to sweep all five golds at one nationals since Dominique Dawes in 1994.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 925, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_Dawes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dominique Dawes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_Dawes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_Dawes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles' only major error among eight events between Friday and Sunday was on a vault on Sunday.\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 1045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She over-rotated a double back-flipping vault that's named after her and fell backward.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She smiled as she walked off, then hit her next vault.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am kind of a veteran; it's not my first time out there,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1260, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am a little bit older, so I know exactly how to kind of reboot and recollect myself to move onto the next event even if I feel like something wasn't how I wanted it to go.\\\"\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. Championships marked the last major competition before the Olympic Trials, which are June 27-30 in Minneapolis.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.8581582794952675, \"rank\": 0.038961038961052005, \"text\": \"Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}, {\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999999998367457, \"rank\": 1.6329270677255594e-10, \"text\": \"Minneapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The trials all-around winner makes the team for the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A three-person selection committee picks the other four team members after trials, taking into account results dating back to last fall's world championships.\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Blakely's Olympic stock rose significantly at nationals.\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was fourth in the all-around last year, then moved up to second this week thanks in part to upgrading her vault.\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I know what I am capable of now,\\\" said Blakely, who met her goal of making the podium and scoring at least 56 points each day (57.05, 56.8).\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Blakely debuted a Cheng vault, adding six tenths of difficulty both nights.\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, a 16-year-old Blakely tied for seventh in her senior nationals debut as the youngest woman in the top 16.\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Tokyo Olympic Trials, she tore an elbow ligament warming up for vault, her first event, and withdrew.\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2404, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She underwent Tommy John surgery.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2419, \"end\": 2437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulnar_collateral_ligament_reconstruction\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommy John surgery\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulnar_collateral_ligament_reconstruction\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulnar_collateral_ligament_reconstruction\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blakely came back to make the last two world championships teams.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Suni Lee, the Tokyo Olympic all-around champion, also bolstered her Paris hopes.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2507, \"end\": 2515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999994542577, \"rank\": 5.457341524390288e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a fall on her opening vault -followed by a helpful talk with Simone Biles- she improved her balance beam and uneven bars scores from night one to night two.\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2656, \"end\": 2668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished second and fourth overall on those two events, which may be key for her Olympic hopes.\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2851, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee is coming back after being diagnosed with two kidney diseases early last year.\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2853, \"end\": 2856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4771217438180882e-14, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been in remission since late 2023.\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2978, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another Olympic team contender, Shilese Jones, did not compete at nationals due to a right shoulder injury but said she plans to be full strength for trials.\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 3137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3012, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shilese Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jones won all-around silver and bronze at the last two world championships and was runner-up to Biles at last year's nationals.\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3270, \"end\": 3280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9996858499193123, \"rank\": 0.0003142488018133685, \"text\": \"A Div